---
description: Frontend structure and JS conventions for 1affiliate
globs:
  - "index.html"
  - "components/**/*.html"
  - "css/**/*.css"
  - "js/**/*.js"
alwaysApply: true
---

### HTML and component rules

- Treat files under `components/` as HTML partials injected into placeholders in `index.html`; **do not change root IDs/classes** without updating all consumers in `js/main.js`.
- Keep Tailwind CDN `<script>` and external `<link>` tags in `<head>` intact unless explicitly asked to change the design system.
- Preserve semantic structure and accessibility where possible when modifying sections or adding new content.

### JavaScript rules

- All JS must run directly in the browser with no build step (no `import`/`export`, CommonJS, or bundler-specific syntax).
- Use plain functions and simple patterns for namespacing; avoid adding unnecessary globals.
- When touching authentication/session logic in `auth.js`, keep the contract with the Apps Script `SCRIPT_URL` and the `email`, `token`, and `nama` fields returned from the backend.
- Avoid hard-coding any secret API keys into the client; follow the existing Gemini canvas pattern and let the environment/user provide keys when needed.

### Performance and UX

- Prefer lazy initialization of heavy UI or network features after page load.
- Keep error messages and UX feedback in clear Indonesian language.
- Maintain the existing modern, Tailwind-based look and feel when extending UI components.
